vLLM-Moet
Copyright 2026 the vLLM-Moet authors

This product includes software developed for serving DeepSeek-V4-Flash on a single
SM120 GPU: 2-bit MoE expert quantization, an FP4 "delta" tier, and hand-written SASS
kernels (the `cubit` toolchain).

Built on and incorporating:

- vLLM (https://github.com/vllm-project/vllm), Apache License 2.0,
  Copyright contributors to the vLLM project. The base is the official tag v0.19.2rc0;
  `patch/vllm-moet.patch` is applied on top of it. That patch also carries the DeepSeek-V4
  model support + sparse-MLA / MTP / indexer + SM120 enablement, which were authored by
  vLLM contributors and the base-fork (kacper-daftcode) authors — not by this project.
  This project's own contribution is the 2-bit MoE + FP4 delta + the cubit kernels.

- DeepGEMM (https://github.com/deepseek-ai/DeepGEMM) is referenced by the base for
  Hopper/Blackwell-DC FP8 paths; it is not used or redistributed here (it has no SM120
  backend — this project uses CUTLASS/Triton/cubit paths on SM120 instead).

- The DeepSeek-V4-Flash model weights are NOT included or redistributed. Obtain the
  official checkpoint separately; the 2-bit planes are built from it at load time.

cubit (the SASS assembler and the hand-written kernels under `kernels/`) and the 2-bit
MoE + FP4-delta quantization (`patch/vllm-new-files/`) are the original contribution of
this project.
